At her current job, Maisy earns 8 hours * $10 per hour = $<<8*10=80>>80.
At her new job, she would earn 4 hours * $15 per hour = $<<4*15=60>>60.
Including her bonus, her new job would pay $60 wage + $35 bonus = $<<60+35=92>>92.
So at her new job, she would earn an extra 92 - 80 = $<<92-80=12>>12.
